spans.text: are the sprightly scenes by Spring supplied , The May-flowered hedges scenting every breeze
The May-flowered hedges scenting every breeze
our fancy thus returns , To former scenes that little pleased when here
lands then restless fancy flies , Where Indian streams through green Savannahs flow
Truth these fairer happier lands survey
Truth these fairer happier lands survey
oft as toiling in the mazy fields , Or homeward passing on the shadeless way
OH whence this wondrous turn of mind our fate
Whatever the season or the place
Why else , when heard in evening's solemn gloom
sounding over the plain Tolls some poor lifeless body to the tomb
No more these eyelids open on the day
thy joyless reign , Thy threatening skies in dusky horrors dressed
an Eden for a transient guest
The clear calm aether at the close of day
the advantage storms and clouds bestow , When blustering Caurus purifies the air , When moist Aquarius pours the fleecy snow , That makes the impregnate glebae a richer harvest bear
him whose mandate spoke the world to form
